│ ### 1. Understanding the Issue                                                             │
│                                                                                            │
│ The LLVM SLP Vectorizer is crashing with an assertion failure `isa<Instruction>(Val)`      │
│ inside the `collectValuesToDemote` function. This assertion indicates that the code is     │
│ attempting to `cast` an LLVM `Value` to an `Instruction`, but the `Value` is not actually  │
│ an `Instruction`. This typically happens when dealing with `Value`s that can be constants, │
│ arguments, or other non-instruction entities.                                              │
│                                                                                            │
│ ### 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log                                                               │
│                                                                                            │
│ The `opt` log shows that the SLP vectorizer is attempting to vectorize a group of `phi`    │
│ nodes in the `if.end7` basic block:                                                        │
│ - `%w.4 = phi i32 [ %w.2, %t ], [ %w.2, %t.u_crit_edge ], [ %bf.cast25, %while.body ]`     │
│ - `%a.4 = phi i32 [ 0, %t ], [ %conv57, %t.u_crit_edge ], [ %bf.cast2910, %while.body ]`   │
│ - `%b.4 = phi i32 [ 0, %t ], [ 0, %t.u_crit_edge ], [ %bf.cast2910, %while.body ]`         │
│ - `%c.4 = phi i32 [ 0, %t ], [ 1, %t.u_crit_edge ], [ poison, %while.body ]`               │
│                                                                                            │
│ The crash occurs during the cost analysis phase, specifically in                           │
│ `computeMinimumValueSizes`, which calls `collectValuesToDemote`. This function analyzes    │
│ the operands of the instructions being vectorized. The `phi` nodes have incoming values    │
│ from different basic blocks. Some of these incoming values are constants (e.g., `i32 0`,   │
│ `i32 1`) or function arguments (e.g., `i32 %conv57`), which are not `Instruction`s.        │
│                                                                                            │
│ ### 3. Root Cause Analysis                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ The backtrace points to a lambda function within `collectValuesToDemote`. This lambda is   │
│ used to check properties of the operands of the instructions being vectorized.             │
│                                                                                            │
│ The crash happens at `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp:17802`. The code at  │
│ this location is inside a lambda passed to `all_of`:                                       │
│ ```cpp                                                                                     │
│ // from collectValuesToDemote                                                              │
│ auto CheckAllOps = [&](unsigned I, unsigned J) {                                           │
