│ `collectValuesToDemote`, a function responsible for analyzing the costs and properties of  │
│ values in the vectorization tree. This function iterates over the operands of the          │
│ instructions it's trying to vectorize.\n\n### 3. Root Cause Analysis\n\nThe backtrace      │
│ points to a lambda function inside `collectValuesToDemote` at `SLPVectorizer.cpp:17802`.   │
│ However, due to inlining and compiler optimizations, the line number in the backtrace can  │
│ be misleading. Looking at the surrounding code, there is a lambda named `IsInstruction`    │
│ that is used to validate operands:\n\n```cpp\n//                                           │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp around line 17785\nauto IsInstruction =    │
│ [&](Value *V) {\n  if (!V)\n    return true;\n  auto *I = cast<Instruction>(V); // Unsafe  │
│ cast!\n  return isValidElementType(I->getType());\n};\n```\n\nThis lambda is called via    │
│ `std::all_of` on the operands of the `phi` nodes. When it encounters the function argument │
│ `%conv57`, the `cast<Instruction>(V)` fails because `V` is an `Argument`, not an           │
│ `Instruction`, leading to the assertion failure.\n\nThe fix is to guard the cast with an   │
│ `isa<Instruction>` check. If the value is not an instruction, the lambda should return     │
│ `false` to indicate that this operand kind is not suitable for this particular analysis    │
│ path.\n\n### 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)\n\nThe edit is to modify the `IsInstruction` lambda │
│ in `collectValuesToDemote` to make it safe.\n\n**File**:                                   │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp`\n**Original Lines (approx.               │
│ 17788-17789)**:\n```cpp\n      auto *I = cast<Instruction>(V);\n      return               │
│ isValidElementType(I->getType());\n```\n\n**Proposed Change**:\n```cpp\n      if           │
│ (!isa<Instruction>(V))\n        return false;\n      auto *I = cast<Instruction>(V);\n     │
